race.description: Soul Food Design Deport & Gallery Maiden Plate
race.comment: BARON OF BUTTER (2) raced very wide but didn't give up and was only beaten 2.5 lengths on debut over this course and distance three weeks ago. Big chance with some natural improvement to come. Four-year-old debutant HARRY (4) looks the danger on the back of a strong recent trial win at this track. Well found in early markets and the son of Bel Esprit looks smart enough to justify the quote. Locally trained BUSTED BUTTONS (7) is another first starter who has come up short in early betting. The confidence comes from a close third in a recent trial at this track. Beautifully drawn so he should have no excuses. FORTIANS (3) overcame a slow start to finish fourth when resuming over this trip at Orange last start. Likely improver with top three prospects. Market watch on another newcomer in MISS STRATEGIC (10) who has had just one quiet trial leading into this.
